The paper deals with distributed graph problems, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on locally checkable labeling problems (LCLs) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. The use of randomness in distributed algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
